The paper deals with developing a model for behavioral robot navigation using natural language instructions, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The model utilizes a modified R-NET with attention mechanisms, which involves natural language processing (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.AI). The paper also involves optimization and combinatorial problems, which are relevant to the optimization (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the model involves processing visual information, which is relevant to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category.
